rComments: Prof Tahamasebi was a great prof. She ensured that students understood key concepts and ensured her students were engaged in her lectures. There was 1 assignment at 35%, another assignment at 30%, and the final exam at 35%. She tells you what to study for the exam. It's good to come to class so you have supplementary information. Great TA and class

Dr. Tahmasebi is a lovely and passionate professor, anyone would be lucky to even sit in one of her lectures. Her course made me re-think the path I wanted to take in university. Her lectures are amazing and are rarely ever boring. Also, the grading is pretty consistent with the marking scheme (with our TA). All in all, great prof, great course!
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Graded by few things']

rComments: I wish her lectures related to the readings! There are soo many. The class is good though - as long as you get a good TA!
Her lectures can seem a bit boring, but she tries to make it interesting. You need to do the readings, and participate in tutorials. The paper was okay. She is very approachable and helpful.

This prof is amazing. She is one of the nicest profs at the scarborough campus. She is very helpful, and will go out of her way to help you. i have taken 5 classes with her so far, and i am again taking one more next semester!!

The course was kind of interesting..the lectures were boring most of the time. she tried to create large class discussions. at times they were helpful but once 7pm hit, everyone just wanted to go home. read the articles. she's kind of hard to understand but you'll get use to it
